Title: Holographic Description of Heavy-Quark Potentials in an Inflationary  Braneworld Scenario
Authors: Luciano Barosi and Francisco A. Brito and Amilcar R. Queiroz
Abstract: We study heavy-quark potential in an inflationary braneworld scenario. The scenario we consider is an (Euclidean) inflating braneworld $AdS_4$ embedded in a static Euclidean $AdS_5$. Using gauge/gravity duality we obtain a confining phase depending on the ratio between the Hubble parameter $H$ in the braneworld and the brane tension $\sigma$.
